In Liquid, you can include a hyphen in your tag syntax `{{ 'e3stLCAtfX0sIHslLSwgYW5kIC0lfQ==' | base64_decode }}` to strip whitespace from the left or right side of a rendered tag.

Normally, even if it doesn’t output text, any line of Liquid in your template will still output a blank line in your rendered HTML:

#### Input
```liquid
{% raw %}
{% assign my_variable = "tomato" %}
{{ my_variable }}
{% endraw %}
```

Notice the blank line before “tomato” in the rendered template:

#### Output

<pre class="raw-output">

tomato
</pre>

## Strip whitespace in assign

By including hyphens in your `assign` tag, you can strip the generated whitespace from the rendered template:

#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
{%- assign my_variable = "tomato" -%}
{{ my_variable }}
{% endraw %}
```

#### Output

<pre class="raw-output">
tomato
</pre>

If you don’t want any of your tags to output whitespace, as a general rule you can add hyphens to both sides of all your tags (`{{ 'eyUtIGFuZCAtJX0=' | base64_decode }}`):

#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% assign username = "John G. Chalmers-Smith" %}
{% if username and username.size > 10 %}
  Wow, {{ username }}, you have a long name!
{% else %}
  Hello there!
{% endif %}
{% endraw %}
```

#### Output without whitespace control


<pre class="raw-output">


  Wow, John G. Chalmers-Smith, you have a long name!

</pre>

#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
{%- assign username = "John G. Chalmers-Smith" -%}
{%- if username and username.size > 10 -%}
  Wow, {{ username }}, you have a long name!
{%- else -%}
  Hello there!
{%- endif -%}
{% endraw %}
```

#### Output with whitespace control

<pre class="raw-output">
Wow, John G. Chalmers-Smith, you have a long name!
</pre>

